{"parse":{"title":"Scholomance","pageid":13963,"wikitext":{"*":"{{stub/Location}}\n:''Were you looking for info on the original version of [[Scholomance (original)|Scholomance]] before the update with {{mists-inline}} Mists of Pandaria?''\n{{infobox instance\n|name=Scholomance\n|aka=Scholo \n|ss=Scholomance loading screen.jpg\n|caption=Scholomance loading graphic\n|loc=[[Caer Darrow]], [[Western Plaguelands]]\n|race={{Race|Cultist}}<br />{{Race|Scourge }}\n|leader={{npc||Ras Frostwhisper}}, {{npc||Araj the Summoner}}, this succeeded by {{npc||Darkmaster Gandling}} \n|boss={{mob|boss=|Darkmaster Gandling}}\n|type=Normal, Heroic\n|level=38 - 48\n|hlevel=90\n|minilvl=440\n|minlevel=33\n|minqlevel=38\n|players=5\n|key=\n|bosses={{Scholomance}}\n}}\n[[File:Scholoban.jpg|thumb|The banner of Scholomance]]\n\nThe '''Scholomance''' (SKOH-loh-mance), a vile academy for prospective necromancers of the [[Scourge]], is located in the ruins of the palatial House of Barov, on a rise overlooking the abandoned city of [[Caer Darrow]]. The enemy level range is 40 - 43 and requires that you be at least level 33 to enter (level 38 to queue via [[Dungeon Finder]]).\n\nMany mini-bosses were removed when the instance was revamped for {{mists-inline}} Mists of Pandaria.\n\nPrior to being re-tuned for a lower level range with [[Patch 4.0.3a]], Scholomance was probably the single most efficient pre-{{bc-inline}} instance for farming, with trash runs up to the Great Ossuary taking about 45 minutes for a fast player, and potentially yielding {{cost|100-200}}, depending on which {{quality|rare}} items dropped.  The instance had a very rich loot table for the level range, and individual mobs tended to drop good amounts of both coins and {{loot|common|Runecloth}}, which generally sold well on the Auction House.  In addition, [[Scholomance Necromancer|necromancers]] and [[Scholomance Dark Summoner|dark summoners]] (as well as a few of the bosses) dropped the prized {{loot|uncommon|Dark Rune|Dark Runes}}, which were useful for raiders and could command prices of {{cost|15-20}} each on the Auction House.  It was not uncommon for 3-4 to drop during a single run, adding potentially another {{cost|80}} to the instance's yield.\n\n== History ==\nThe Scholomance was founded by the rogue wizard {{npc||Kel'Thuzad}} nearly ten years ago. His [[Cult of the Damned]] renovated the ancient crypts beneath Caer Darrow (an old Arathorian fortress) and turned them into a school for necromancy. The Cult used this place to train its mortal agents and prepare to unleash the [[Plague of Undeath]] upon [[Lordaeron]]. It has been brewing with young talented wizards and adepts all this time. No one in Lordaeron knew. Originally, the Barov family (of [[Alterac Mountains|Alterac]]) owned the land and gave it to the Cult in exchange for the [[Lich King]]'s blessing of immortality. Now the Barovs remain as undead monsters. One of Kel'Thuzad's mightiest agents, the [[Ravenian]], also lives within the recesses of the school &mdash; ever ready to devour those students who show any sign of weakness. The [[lich]] {{npc||Ras Frostwhisper}} rules over the site and guards it for the Scourge, but the mortal necromancer, {{npc||Darkmaster Gandling}}, serves as headmaster of the school, succeeding {{npc||Araj the Summoner}} who was headmaster after Kel'thuzad.\n\n{{wow-dungeons}}\n:''The Scholomance is housed within a series of crypts that lie beneath the ruined keep of [[Caer Darrow]]. Once owned by the noble [[Barov]] family, Caer Darrow fell into ruin following the [[Second War]]. As the wizard [[Kel'thuzad]] enlisted followers for his [[Cult of the Damned]], he would often promise immortality in exchange for serving the Lich King. The Barov family fell to Kel'thuzad's charismatic influence and donated the keep and its crypts to the [[Scourge]]. The cultists then killed the Barovs and turned the ancient crypts into a school for necromancy known as the Scholomance. Though Kel'thuzad no longer resides in the crypts, devoted cultists and instructors still remain. The powerful lich, [[Ras Frostwhisper]], rules over the site and guards it in the Scourge's name &mdash; while the mortal necromancer, Darkmaster Gandling, serves as the school's insidious headmaster.''\n\n=== In Mists of Pandaria ===\n{{mists-section}}\n{{sectionstub}}\n\n=== In Cataclysm ===\n{{cata-section}}\n{{sectionstub}}\n\n=== Difficulty pre-Cataclysm ===\nAt release, Scholomance was an extremely challenging dungeon. Typically, the dungeon was raided in 10-man parties, with a difficulty similar to [[Upper Blackrock Spire]]. Subsequent patches in the summer of 2006 changed Scholomance drastically. Mobs were weakened slightly, and a great many were removed. However, Scholomance could no longer be run with more than 5 party members. At the time, this \"Scholo [[Nerf]]\" was a common topic for party chat among long-time players. Loot in Scholomance has changed gradually over time. Originally, each boss dropped some relatively weak loot. The dungeon waned in popularity as players saw little point in running it after they had completed their quests and acquired their [[Dungeon Set 1]] hat. Blizzard again patched the dungeon. At this point, Scholomance dropped a moderate amount of fairly useful items, including a very small chance at the epic {{loot|Epic|Headmaster's Charge}} and {{loot|Epic|Alanna's Embrace}}. The rewards available from the [[Argent Dawn]] also broadened through patches. Scholomance was a staple source of Argent Dawn reputation and [[Scourgestone]]s. Players seeking [[Argent Dawn]] tradeskill recipes, resistance enchantments or [[Argent Dawn#Armaments of the Dawn|Armaments of the Dawn]] often spent a great deal of time in Scholomance or [[Stratholme]].\n\n== Geography ==\n=== Maps ===\n<gallery>\nFile:WorldMap-Scholomance1.jpg|The Reliquary\nFile:WorldMap-Scholomance2.jpg|Chamber of Summoning\nFile:WorldMap-Scholomance3.jpg|The Upper Study\nFile:WorldMap-Scholomance4.jpg|Headmaster's Study\n</gallery>\n\n=== Sub-regions ===\n{{Accuracy-section}}\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|[[Barov Family Vault]]{{\u00b7}} [[Chamber of Summoning]]{{\u00b7}} [[The Coven]]{{\u00b7}} [[The Great Ossuary]]{{\u00b7}} [[Hall of Secrets]]{{\u00b7}} [[Hall of the Damned]]{{\u00b7}} [[Headmaster's Study]]{{\u00b7}} [[The Laboratory]]{{\u00b7}} [[Reliquary (Scholomance)|The Reliquary]]{{\u00b7}} [[Shadow Vault (Scholomance)|The Shadow Vault]]{{\u00b7}} [[The Viewing Room]]{{\u00b7}} [[Vault of the Ravenian]]\n|}\n\n== Quests ==\n=== In Scholomance ===\n{{sectionstub}}\n\n== Dungeon denizens ==\n{{sectionstub}}\n\n=== NPC and quest givers ===\n* {{NPC||Talking Skull|level=1}}\n\n=== Mobs ===\n;The Students\n{{sectionstub}}\n* {{mob|Bored Student|level=41 - 91+}}\n* {{mob|Candlestick Mage|Illusionist Apprentice|level=41 - 91+}}\n* {{mob|Failed Student|level=43 - 93}}\n* {{mob|Scholomance Acolyte|level=41 - 91+}}\n* {{mob|Scholomance Neophyte|level=41 - 91+}}\n\n;Workers\n{{sectionstub}}\n* {{NPC||Boneweaver|level=42 - 92+}}\n\n;Experimental victims\n* {{NPC||Fresh Test Subject|level=41 - 90}}\n* {{mob|Expired Test Subject|level=41 - 90}}\n* {{mob|Meat Graft|level=41 - 91}}\n\n;Mindless Undead\n{{sectionstub}}\n* {{mob|Bound Servant|level=41 - 91+}}\n* {{mob|Brittle Skeleton|level=41 - 91}}\n* {{mob|Flesh Horror|level=42 - 92+}}\n* {{mob|Reanimated Corpse|level=41 - 91}}\n* {{mob|Skeleton|level=1}}\n* {{mob|Soul Fragment|level=41 - 91+}}\n\n;Undead\n{{sectionstub}}\n* {{mob|Krastinovian Carver|level=41 - 91+}}\n* {{mob|Risen Guard|level=42 - 92+}}\n* {{mob|Woven Boneguard|level=41 - 91+}}\n\n=== Bosses and Mini Bosses ===\n{{sectionstub}}\n* {{mob|Putridius|level=40 <small>Rare</small>}}\n* {{mob|Professor Slate|Potions Master|level=42 - 92+}} for {{item|icon=|Empty Polyformic Acid Vial}}\n* {{mob|boss=|Instructor Chillheart|level=43 - 93+}}\n** {{mob|Instructor Chillheart's Phylactery|level=43 - 93+}}\n* {{mob|Jandice Barov|level=43 - 92+}}\n* {{mob|boss=|Rattlegore|level=43 - 93+}}\n** {{mob|boss=|Doctor Theolen Krastinov|The Butcher|level=91+ <small>Rare</small>}} ''[[Heroic mode]] only''\n* {{mob|boss=|Lilian Voss|level=43 - 92+}}\n** {{mob|Lilian Voss|level=43 - 93+}}\n** {{mob|Lilian's Soul|level=43 - 93+}}\n* {{mob|boss=|Darkmaster Gandling|level=43 - 93+}}\n\n== Loot ==\nSee [[Scholomance loot]].\n\n== Scholomance faculty ==\n{{Speculation}}\n*{{NPC||Darkmaster Gandling}} &mdash; School Headmaster\n*{{NPC||Ras Frostwhisper}} &mdash; School Chairman, Alchemy\n*{{NPC||Doctor Theolen Krastinov}} &mdash; Torturer, Anatomy, Demonology\n*{{NPC||Lorekeeper Polkelt}} &mdash; Librarian, History\n*{{NPC||Instructor Malicia}} &mdash; Occultism, Shadow Magic\n*{{NPC||Vectus}} &mdash; Arcane Magic\n*{{NPC||Ravenian}} &mdash; Janitor, Corporal Punishment\n*{{NPC||Jandice Barov}} &mdash; Zombification, Corpse Control, Plague Research\n* Professor Slate &#x2014; Potions\n\n== Notes ==\n*As of {{mists-inline}} Mists of Pandaria, no key is required to enter the instance.{{fact}}\n*In ''[[Lands of Conflict]]'', Scholomance is said to be below Andorhal, while the narrator was not able to explore Caer Darrow.\n*Non-Boss high elves in the instance still use the old model based on Night elven models rather than the ones based on Blood elven models.\n*Near Ras Frostwhisper is one of two [[Alchemy Lab]]s known to exist in Azeroth, the other is in [[Blackwing Lair]]. However, for ''[[The Burning Crusade]]'' players, there are Alchemy Labs in [[Shattrath City]] and [[Sun's Reach]].\n\n== Trivia ==\n*According to Romanian legend, a real {{wplink|Scholomance}} exists by an unnamed lake in the mountains south of the city of Hermannstadt (called Sibiu in Romanian) in Transylvania. This school of black magic is said to be run by the Devil, and would accept only ten students at a time. The tenth would remain to serve the Devil as payment for his teachings. The Scholomance in WoW is placed in the middle of the lake, much like its legendary namesake. In Bram Stoker's ''Dracula'', Count Dracula is said to have spent several years training under the Devil in the Scholomance. It is referenced in both Stoker's novel and an article titled \"Transylvanian Superstitions\" on page 136 of ''The Nineteenth Century'' by Emily Gerard.\n\n== Trivia ==\n*According to early blue posts: Scholomance was originally thought of as an outdoor non-instanced area, much smaller, where [[Uther's Tomb]] is now. The designers made it so visually stunning that it was turned into an instance, so that it could be moved and enlarged.\n\n== Media ==\n[[File:The Story of Eva Sarkhoff WoW Machinima|thumb|right|335 px]]\n=== Videos ===\n{| class=\"darktable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Wowhead !!MMO Champion\n|-\n|[[File:Scholomance Revamp - Mists of Pandaria Beta|425px]] ||[[File:Scholomance - Heroic Instance Guide|425px]]\n|-\n!Nialinius\n|-\n|[[File:Dungeons & Raids Scholomance|425px]]\n|}\n\n;Circa [[Patch 4.2.2]]\n{| class=\"darktable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Nivarka (1080p, with commentary)\n|-\n|[[File:NivPlay Scholomance Playthough Part 1|280px]]\n|[[File:NivPlay Scholomance Playthough Part 2|280px]]\n|[[File:NivPlay Scholomance Playthough Part 3|280px]]\n|-\n|Scholomance Playthrough Part 1\n|Scholomance Playthrough Part 2\n|Scholomance Playthrough Part 3\n|}\n\n== Patch changes ==\n* {{Patch 5.0.4|note=Scholomance mobs revamped and level 90 heroic version added.}}\n* {{Patch 4.0.3a|note=Level dropped significantly to 38-48}}\n* {{Patch 1.10.0|note=Capped at five players.}}\n* {{Patch 1.6.0|note=Several spawns removed from Scholomance. This should make for a more enjoyable 5 player experience.}}\n* {{Patch 1.4.0|note=\n**20 new Rare items have been added to Scholomance.\n**Several Uncommon items have been upgraded to Rare quality.\n**There is a new load screen for Stratholme.}}\n* {{Patch 1.3.0|note=\n**Capped at ten players.\n**Lengthened the respawn time of many of the creatures in Scholomance.\n**Characters dying in the instanced portions of Scholomance will now correctly receive a corpse marker in the minimap and see the message letting them know that they need to enter the instance before they will be able to resurrect.}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Scholomance (original)]]\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Read http://www.wowwiki.com/WoWWiki:External_links before posting your links here.\nLinks that do not conform to the rules will be DELETED.\nRepeat violations may result in a BAN.\nHave a nice day. :) -->\n{{bnetwowinstance|Scholomance}}\n{{elinks-zone|6066}}\n\n;Guides\n{{elink|icon=icyveinscom|site=Icy Veins|link=http://www.icy-veins.com/scholomance-wow-heroic-dungeon-guide|desc=Scholomance Walkthrough (Bosses, Achievements, Loot, and Quests)}}\n\n;News\n{{elink|type=wowheadnews|link=http://www.wowhead.com/news=204817/mists-of-pandaria-loot-tables-and-dungeon-journals|desc=Mists of Pandaria Loot Tables and Dungeon Journals|bydate=by [http://www.wowhead.com/news&user=Ashelia Ashelia] 2012/07/18 1:52 PM}}\n{{elink|type=mmochampion|link=http://www.mmo-champion.com/content/2821-Account-Wide-Mounts-Challenge-Mode-Valor-Rewards-Heroic-Scholomance-Blue-Posts|desc=Account Wide Mounts, Challenge Mode Valor Rewards, Heroic Scholomance, Blue Posts|bydate=by [http://www.mmo-champion.com/members/523085-chaud chaud] 2012-06-26 06:45 AM}}\n{{elink|type=wowinsider|link=http://wow.joystiq.com/2012/03/19/mists-of-pandaria-dungeon-preview/|desc=Mists of Pandaria: Dungeons and challenge mode|bydate=by {{wowinsider|Alex Ziebart}} Mar 19th 2012 at 3:01AM}}\n\n\n{{Scholomance Subzones}}\n{{Dungeons}}\n\n[[de:Scholomance]]\n[[es:Scholomance]]\n[[fr:Scholomance]]\n[[ja:Scholomance]]\n[[pl:Scholomance]]\n[[ru:\u041d\u0435\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442]]\n\n[[Category:Instances]]\n[[Category:Ruins]]\n[[Category:Scholomance| ]]\n[[Category:Western Plaguelands]]\n[[Category:Crypts]]\n[[Category:Organizations]]"}}}